                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d546">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 656.119/488e</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Minister in the Netherlands</hi> (<persName
                        corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_GJW1" type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Garrett</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-05-20T18:00:00-04:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">May 20, 1918, 6 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1222. You may informally advise the Minister of Foreign Affairs that this
                    Government, in view of its offer to place at the disposal of the Government of
                    the Netherlands 50,000 tons of bread cereal in <pb facs="0660" n="1494"
                        xml:id="pg_1494"/> United States, has been endeavoring to accumulate such
                    bread cereal at convenient ports in order that there might be as little delay as
                    possible when ships from Dutch ports would reach here for the purpose of lifting
                    such cereal. We are in position today to supply at once at ports 15,000 tons of
                    such cereals. We can not, however, maintain this situation indefinitely, and
                    suggest that if delay in loading Dutch ships is to be avoided in the future
                    Dutch ships should promptly be dispatched from Netherlands ports and this
                    Government advised as to their probable dates of arrival. Report result of
                    informal conference promptly.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_LR1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Lansing</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
